  "doc_id": "28463",
  "text": "The mass transfer rate prediction performance of 24 different enhancement factor models was evaluated against 601 data points in four data sets from two wetted wall columns, a laminar jet contactor and a string of discs contactor. Predictions were also compared with results from a discretized penetration model used in developing concentration based and activity based reaction kinetic models for MEA by Putta et al. [CITATION_1] . The data sets cover MEA concentrations from 0.5 -9 moles/L, CO2 loadings from 0 -0.5 moles CO2/mole MEA and temperatures from 293-343K. It is deemed important to use data from experiments where the interfacial area is well defined in order to avoid uncertainties in area predictions.",
